ZCZC GE59
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 232300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS
THE UK. A SHALLOW LOW CENTRED SERN NORWAY BRINGS STRG
WINDS TO THE CENTRAL N SEA. OVERNIGHT SATURDAY HIGH
PRESSURE MOVS E INTO THE N SEA WITH STRG WINDS EASING.
DURING SUNDAY A LOW W OF THE UK MOVS E WITH STRG WINDS
SPREADING TO THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AND SERN N SEA AS FAR N
AS DOGGER. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY THE LOW MOVS NE WITH STRG
WINDS SPREADING TO THE NERN N SEA BUT EASING IN THE
ENGLISH CHANNEL. HIGH PRESSURE BEGINS TO BUILD IN THE W.
DURING MONDAY THE LOW BECOMES SLOW MOV CENTRED S UTSIRE
AND FILLS THOUGH STRG WINDS PERSIST FOR ALL BUT THE FAR
S OF THE N SEA. OVERNIGHT MONDAY THE LOW CONTINUES TO
FILL WITH STRG WINDS EASING IN THE N SEA. DURING TUESDAY
HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS ACROSS THE N SEA WHILST A NEW LOW W
OF THE UK BRINGS STRG WINDS TO FAIR ISLE
